<font color="#FF0000">WHY VIETNAM AND NOT NIGERIA?</font><br>
<tt>Mon Feb  3 22:29:35 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Speaking of Nigeria, at the same time as the Vietnam War, the Nigerian Civil War was going on in the late 60's.  The U.S. government didn't intervene to help the Ibo of the Republic of Biafra to win their independence.  Why not?  They wanted to be free just like the South Vietnamese, didn't they?  The reason is simply that the Russians weren't a factor there so that our government didn't care.  Of course the American people didn't care either, but did they really &quot;care&quot; about Vietnam either?
